.TH DP_PERFORM_DETAILED_STREAMING_COMPLETION 3 "March 13, 2026" "libdisasterparty @DP_VERSION@" "Disaster Party Manual"

.SH NAME
dp_perform_detailed_streaming_completion \- perform a streaming completion with detailed event handling

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include <disasterparty.h>
.PP
.BI "int dp_perform_detailed_streaming_completion(dp_context_t *" context ", const dp_request_config_t *" request_config ", dp_detailed_stream_callback_t " callback ", void *" user_data ", dp_response_t *" response ");"

.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B dp_perform_detailed_streaming_completion()
function sends a request to the configured LLM provider and streams the response
via a series of detailed events. It is a cross-provider generalization of the
original Anthropic-specific streaming function.

The
.I callback
is invoked for various SSE events such as start, content deltas, thinking blocks,
and stop signals.

.SH CALLBACK SIGNATURE
.nf
typedef int (*dp_detailed_stream_callback_t)(const dp_stream_event_t* event,
                                              void* user_data,
                                              const char* error_during_stream);
.fi

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR dp_perform_streaming_completion (3),
.BR dp_enable_advanced_features (3),
.BR disasterparty (7)
